summary: avengers as shit i’ve heard at school
title: avengers as shit i’ve heard at school
body:
tony: poetry is for people stuck in the 1940s.

steve: *in response to “everyone i know is gay”* i’m half gay!

natasha: he asked me out. i slapped him.

thor: yeah, then my brother threw me out of the window.

bruce: life is hard. then you die.

clint: look at me, i’m a blind mouse! *pulls hoodie over face*

peter: my cat’s better than yours! my cat’s instagram famous!

wanda: you thought i already screwed up? oh, wait till you hear what i did next.

bucky: i need to stop meeting people.

summary: Leah bb headcannon about Tony and the “don’t hand me stuff” thing: he still doesn’t like it when Peter does it, but doesn’t say...
question: Leah bb headcannon about Tony and the “don’t hand me stuff” thing: he still doesn’t like it when Peter does it, but doesn’t say anything bc he loves him thank you for your time
answer:
OOF okay so I honestly think that Tony doesn’t like it AT FIRST like when they first meet and are just starting to get to know each other but once they are both comfortable, Tony actually starts to ASK Peter to hand him things–they are in the lab and Tony needs to screw driver or they are getting ice cream and Tony needs a spoon 

Peter doesn’t realize how big this is until Steve tries to hand Tony some paper work about the new training schedule and Tony just straight up doesn’t take it and tells Cap to put it on the table instead. 

When Peter asks about it, Tony just looks at him and says “kiddo, I give you so much stuff, the least you can do is return the favor” 

and Peter just fucking bursts out laughing and after a second, so does Tony and he like pulls Peter closer and ruffles his hair and then they eat pizza and the whole time Tony just makes Peter hand him things and Peter is laughing and Tony is smiling a real smile for the first time in a while and its pure and soft and I Stan.
